    },
    {
        "Lord Beaverbrook": "Lord Beaverbrook"
    },
    {
        ". The agnostic Aitken liked to tease the Methodist Bennett, whose fiery temper contrasted with Aitkens ability to turn away wrath with a joke. This friendship would become important to his success later in life, as would his friendship with the ": null
    },
    {
        "Chatham": "Chatham, New Brunswick"
    },
    {
        " lawyer, ": null
    },
    {
        "Lemuel J. Tweedie": "Lemuel J. Tweedie"
    },
    {
