    },
    {
        "E. B. Eddy Company": "E. B. Eddy Company"
    },
    {
        ", a large ": null
    },
    {
        "pulp and paper": "Pulp And Paper"
    },
    {
        " industrial concern, and was transferred to ": null
    },
    {
        "Halifax": "City Of Halifax"
    },
    {
        ". His sister moved there to study nursing, and soon Bennett joined them to study law at ": null
    },
    {
        "Dalhousie University": "Dalhousie University"
    },
    {
        ". Their friendship was renewed there, and became crucial to his later life when Jennie Shirreff married the head of the Eddy Company. She later made Bennett the lawyer for her extensive interests.       Bennett started at ": null
    },
    {
        "Dalhousie University": "Dalhousie University"
    },
    {
        " in 1890, graduating in 1893 with a law degree and very high standing. He worked his way through with a job as assistant in the library, being recommended by the Dean, Dr. ": null
    },
    {
        "Richard Chapman Weldon": "Richard Chapman Weldon"
    },
    {
        ", MP, and participated in debating and moot court activities. Canadas Prime Ministers: Macdonald to Trudeau , 2007, p. 301     He was then a partner in the Chatham law firm of Tweedie and Bennett. Max Aitken  was his office boy, while ": null
    },
    {
        "articling": "Articling"
    },
    {
        " as a lawyer, acting as a stringer for the ": null
    },
    {
        "Montreal Gazette": "Montreal Gazette"
    },
    {
        ", and selling life insurance. Aitken persuaded him to run for ": null
    },
    {
        "alderman": "Alderman"
    },
    {
        " in the first Town Council of Chatham, and managed his campaign. Bennett was elected by one vote, and was later furious with Aitken when he heard all the promises he had made on Bennetts behalf.       Despite his election to the Chatham town council, Bennetts days in the town were numbered. He was ambitious and saw that the small community was too narrow a field for him. He was already negotiating with Sir ": null
    },
    {
        "James Lougheed": "James Lougheed"
    },
    {
        " to move to the ": null
